2115	            Notes:
2116	                The response body will be stored regardless of the status code. See the ``Axon.wget()`` API
2117	                documentation to see the complete structure of the response dictionary.
2118	
2119	            Example:
2120	                Get the Vertex Project website::
2121	
2122	                    $headers = ({})
2123	                    $headers."User-Agent" = Foo/Bar
2124	
2125	                    $resp = $lib.axon.wget("http://vertex.link", method=GET, headers=$headers)
2126	                    if $resp.ok { $lib.print("Downloaded: {size} bytes", size=$resp.size) }
2127	            """,

1410	
1411	class GrammarTest(s_t_utils.SynTest):
1412	
1413	    def test_grammar(self):
1414	        '''
1415	        Validates that we have no grammar ambiguities
1416	        '''
1417	        with s_datfile.openDatFile('synapse.lib/storm.lark') as larkf:
1418	            grammar = larkf.read().decode()
1419	
1420	        parser = lark.Lark(grammar, start='query', debug=True, regex=True, parser='lalr',
1421	                           keep_all_tokens=True, maybe_placeholders=False,
1422	                           propagate_positions=True)
1423	
1424	        for term, valu in parser._terminals_dict.items():
1425	            self.false(term.startswith('__ANON'), msg=f'ANON token {valu} present in grammar!')
1426	
1427	        for i, query in enumerate(Queries):
1428	            try:
1429	                tree = parser.parse(query)
1430	                # print(f'#{i}: {query}')
1431	                # print(tree, '\n')
1432	                self.notin('_ambig', str(tree))
1433	
1434	            except (lark.ParseError, lark.UnexpectedCharacters):
1435	                print(f'Failure on parsing #{i}:\n{{{query}}}')
1436	                raise
1437	
1438	    async def test_parser(self):
1439	        self.maxDiff = None
1440	        for i, query in enumerate(Queries):
1441	            parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1442	            tree = parser.query()
1443	            self.eq(str(tree), _ParseResults[i])
1444	
1445	    def test_cmdrargs(self):
1446	        q = '''add {inet:fqdn | graph 2 --filter { -#nope } } inet:f-M +1 { [ meta:note='*' :type=m1]}'''
1447	        correct = (
1448	            'add',
1449	            'inet:fqdn | graph 2 --filter { -#nope }',
1450	            'inet:f-M',
1451	            '+1',
1452	            "[ meta:note='*' :type=m1]"
1453	            )
1454	        parser = s_parser.Parser(q)
1455	        args = parser.cmdrargs()
1456	        self.eq(args, correct)
1457	
1458	        q = 'add --filter={inet:fqdn | limit 1}'
1459	        parser = s_parser.Parser(q)
1460	        args = parser.cmdrargs()
1461	        self.eq(args, ['add', '--filter=inet:fqdn | limit 1'])
1462	
1463	        query = 'add {uniq +#*}'
1464	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1465	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1466	            parser.cmdrargs()
1467	
1468	    def test_mode_lookup(self):
1469	        q = '1.2.3.4 vertex.link | spin'
1470	        parser = s_parser.Parser(q)
1471	        tree = parser.lookup()
1472	        self.eq(str(tree), 'Lookup: [LookList: [Const: 1.2.3.4, Const: vertex.link], '
1473	                           'Query: [CmdOper: [Const: spin, Const: ()]]]')
1474	
1475	        query = '1.2.3.4 | uniq +#*'
1476	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1477	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1478	            parser.lookup()
1479	
1480	    def test_mode_search(self):
1481	        tree = s_parser.parseQuery('foo bar | spin', mode='search')
1482	        self.eq(str(tree), 'Search: [LookList: [Const: foo, Const: bar], '
1483	                           'Query: [CmdOper: [Const: spin, Const: ()]]]')
1484	
1485	        query = '1.2.3.4 | uniq +#*'
1486	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1487	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1488	            parser.search()
1489	
1490	    def test_mode_storm(self):
1491	        # added for coverage of the top level function...
1492	        tree = s_parser.parseQuery('inet:fqdn=vertex.link', mode='storm')
1493	        self.eq(str(tree), 'Query: [LiftPropBy: [Const: inet:fqdn, Const: =, Const: vertex.link]]')
1494	
1495	    def test_mode_autoadd(self):
1496	        # added for coverage of the top level function...
1497	        tree = s_parser.parseQuery('vertex.link', mode='autoadd')
1498	        self.eq(str(tree), 'Lookup: [LookList: [Const: vertex.link]]')
1499	
1500	    def test_parse_float(self):
1501	        self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax, s_grammar.parse_float, 'visi', 0)
1502	        self.eq((4.2, 3), s_grammar.parse_float('4.2', 0))
1503	        self.eq((-4.2, 4), s_grammar.parse_float('-4.2', 0))
1504	        self.eq((-4.2, 8), s_grammar.parse_float('    -4.2', 0))
1505	        self.eq((-4.2, 8), s_grammar.parse_float('    -4.2', 2))
1506	
1507	    def test_nom(self):
1508	        self.eq(('xyz', 10), s_grammar.nom('   xyz    ', 0, 'wxyz', trim=True))
1509	
1510	    def test_parse_cmd_string(self):
1511	        self.eq(('newp', 9), s_parser.parse_cmd_string('help newp', 5))
1512	
1513	    async def test_syntax_error(self):
1514	
1515	        query = 'test:str )'
1516	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1517	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1518	            parser.query()
1519	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1520	
1521	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 9)
1522	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1523	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 10)
1524	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token ')' at line 1, column 10"))
1525	
1526	        query = 'test:str {'
1527	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1528	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1529	            parser.query()
1530	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1531	
1532	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 9)
1533	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1534	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 10)
1535	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'end of input' at line 1, column 10"))
1536	
1537	        query = '''function itworks() {
1538	                $lib.print('it works')
1539	                return ( $lib.true )
1540	            }
1541	
1542	            $itworks()
1543	
1544	            function foo(baz=$lib.true, faz) {
1545	                return ( $lib.true )
1546	            }
1547	
1548	            $foo()'''
1549	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1550	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1551	            parser.query()
1552	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1553	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 160)
1554	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 8)
1555	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 25)
1556	        self.eq(errinfo.get('mesg'),
1557	                'Positional parameter "faz" follows keyword parameter in definition')
1558	
1559	        query = '''function foo(bar, baz, bar) { return ( $lib.true ) }'''
1560	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1561	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1562	            parser.query()
1563	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1564	        self.nn(errinfo.get('highlight'))
1565	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 23)
1566	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1567	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 24)
1568	        self.eq(errinfo.get('mesg'),
1569	                'Duplicate parameter "bar" in function definition')
1570	
1571	        query = '''$lib.foo(bar=(1), baz=(2), bar=(3))'''
1572	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1573	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1574	            parser.query()
1575	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1576	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 27)
1577	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1578	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 28)
1579	        self.eq(errinfo.get('mesg'),
1580	                'Duplicate keyword argument "bar" in function call')
1581	
1582	        query = '''$lib.foo(bar=(1), (2), (3))'''
1583	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1584	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1585	            parser.query()
1586	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1587	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 18)
1588	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1589	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 19)
1590	        self.eq(errinfo.get('mesg'),
1591	                "Positional argument follows keyword argument in function call")
1592	
1593	        query = '''
1594	
1595	        { inet:cidr4#rep.some.body
1596	        $lib.print('weee')
1597	        tee { -> :network } }
1598	        '''
1599	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1600	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1601	            parser.query()
1602	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1603	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 81)
1604	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 5)
1605	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 18)
1606	        self.eq(errinfo.get('token'), ':network')
1607	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'relative property name' at line 5, column 18"))
1608	
1609	        query = 'inet:ipv4 | tee { -> foo '
1610	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1611	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1612	            _ = parser.query()
1613	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1614	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 21)
1615	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1616	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 22)
1617	        self.eq(errinfo.get('token'), 'foo')
1618	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'command name' at line 1, column 22"))
1619	
1620	        query = '''// comment
1621	
1622	        #rep.blah.newp +inet:ipv4 --> * <--'''
1623	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1624	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1625	            _ = parser.query()
1626	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1627	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 52)
1628	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 3)
1629	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 41)
1630	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'end of input' at line 3, column 41"))
1631	
1632	        query = '''// comment
1633	
1634	                #rep.blah.newp +inet:ipv4 --> * <-- | help'''
1635	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1636	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1637	            _ = parser.query()
1638	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1639	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 64)
1640	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 3)
1641	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 53)
1642	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token '|' at line 3, column 53"))
1643	
1644	        query = '''$str = $lib.cast(str,(1234))
1645	         if (!$str ~= '3.+0'  ) {
1646	           $lib.print($str)
1647	         }'''
1648	
1649	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1650	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1651	            _ = parser.query()
1652	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1653	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 42)
1654	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 2)
1655	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 14)
1656	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'comparison operator' at line 2, column 14"))
1657	
1658	        query = '''$str = $lib.cast(str, (1234))  if (!$str ~= '3.+0'  ) { $lib.print($str) }'''
1659	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1660	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1661	            _ = parser.query()
1662	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1663	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 35)
1664	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1665	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 36)
1666	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'comparison operator' at line 1, column 36"))
1667	
1668	        query = '''return(({"foo": "bar", "baz": foo}))'''
1669	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1670	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1671	            _ = parser.query()
1672	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1673	        self.eq(errinfo.get('at'), 30)
1674	        self.eq(errinfo.get('line'), 1)
1675	        self.eq(errinfo.get('column'), 31)
1676	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected unquoted string in JSON expression"))
1677	
1678	        query = '''ou:name="foo\x00bar"'''
1679	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1680	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1681	            _ = parser.query()
1682	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1683	        self.eq(errinfo.get('valu'), '\'"foo\\x00bar"\'')
1684	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith('Invalid character in string \'"foo\\x00bar"\''))
1685	
1686	        query = '''#test.*.bar'''
1687	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1688	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1689	            _ = parser.query()
1690	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1691	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token 'default case' at line 1, column 7"))
1692	
1693	        query = '''$foo=(3+foo)'''
1694	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1695	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1696	            _ = parser.query()
1697	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1698	        self.eq(1, errinfo.get('mesg').count('#'))
1699	
1700	        query = '$q = ${ /* secret comment */ $lib.print([hello) } $lib.macro.set(hehe, $q)'
1701	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1702	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1703	            _ = parser.query()
1704	        info = cm.exception.errinfo.get('highlight')
1705	        self.eq((40, 41), info['offsets'])
1706	        self.eq((1, 1), info['lines'])
1707	        self.eq((41, 42), info['columns'])
1708	
1709	        query = """function test(hello) {
1710	                    +'''asdf
1711	                    asdfasdf'''
1712	        }"""
1713	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1714	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1715	            _ = parser.query()
1716	        info = cm.exception.errinfo.get('highlight')
1717	        self.eq((44, 83), info['offsets'])
1718	        self.eq((2, 3), info['lines'])
1719	        self.eq((22, 31), info['columns'])
1720	
1721	        query = '$x=$lib.guid(foo$bar)'
1722	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1723	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1724	            _ = parser.query()
1725	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1726	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token '$' at line 1, column 17"))
1727	
1728	        query = '$x=$lib.guid(foo(bar)'
1729	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1730	        with self.raises(s_exc.BadSyntax) as cm:
1731	            _ = parser.query()
1732	        errinfo = cm.exception.errinfo
1733	        self.true(errinfo.get('mesg').startswith("Unexpected token '(' at line 1, column 17"))
1734	
1735	    async def test_quotes(self):
1736	
1737	        # Test vectors
1738	        queries = ((r'''[test:str="WORDS \"THINGS STUFF.\""]''', 'WORDS "THINGS STUFF."'),
1739	                   (r'''[test:str='WORDS "THINGS STUFF."']''', 'WORDS "THINGS STUFF."'),
1740	                   (r'''[test:str="\""]''', '"'),
1741	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\world!"]''', 'hello\\world!'),
1742	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\\"world!"]''', 'hello\\"world!'),
1743	                   # Single quoted string
1744	                   (r'''[test:str='hello\\\"world!']''', 'hello\\\\\\"world!'),
1745	                   (r'''[test:str='hello\t"world!']''', 'hello\\t"world!'),
1746	                   # TAB
1747	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\tworld!"]''', 'hello\tworld!'),
1748	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\tworld!"]''', 'hello\\tworld!'),
1749	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\\tworld!"]''', 'hello\\\tworld!'),
1750	                   # LF / Newline
1751	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\nworld!"]''', 'hello\nworld!'),
1752	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\nworld!"]''', 'hello\\nworld!'),
1753	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\\nworld!"]''', 'hello\\\nworld!'),
1754	                   # CR / Carriage returns
1755	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\rworld!"]''', 'hello\rworld!'),
1756	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\rworld!"]''', 'hello\\rworld!'),
1757	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\\\rworld!"]''', 'hello\\\rworld!'),
1758	                   # single quote escape
1759	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\'world!"]''', '''hello'world!'''),
1760	                   (r'''[test:str="hello'world!"]''', '''hello'world!'''),  # escape isn't technically required
1761	                   # BEL
1762	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\aworld!"]''', '''hello\aworld!'''),
1763	                   # BS
1764	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\bworld!"]''', '''hello\bworld!'''),
1765	                   # FF
1766	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\fworld!"]''', '''hello\fworld!'''),
1767	                   # VT
1768	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\vworld!"]''', '''hello\vworld!'''),
1769	                   # \xhh - hex
1770	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\xffworld!"]''', '''hello\xffworld!'''),
1771	                   # \ooo - octal
1772	                   (r'''[test:str="hello\040world!"]''', '''hello world!'''),
1773	                   # Items encoded as a python literal object wrapped in quotes
1774	                   # are not turned into their corresponding item, they are
1775	                   # treated as strings.
1776	                   (r'''[test:str="{'key': 'valu'}"]''', '''{'key': 'valu'}'''),
1777	                   )
1778	
1779	        async with self.getTestCore() as core:
1780	            for (query, valu) in queries:
1781	                nodes = await core.nodes(query)
1782	                self.len(1, nodes)
1783	                self.eq(nodes[0].ndef[1], valu)
1784	
1785	    def test_isre_funcs(self):
1786	
1787	        self.true(s_grammar.isCmdName('testcmd'))
1788	        self.true(s_grammar.isCmdName('testcmd2'))
1789	        self.true(s_grammar.isCmdName('testcmd.yup'))
1790	        self.false(s_grammar.isCmdName('2testcmd'))
1791	        self.false(s_grammar.isCmdName('testcmd:newp'))
1792	        self.false(s_grammar.isCmdName('.hehe'))
1793	
1794	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.hehe'))
1795	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.hehe:haha'))
1796	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.hehe.haha'))
1797	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.hehe4'))
1798	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.hehe.4haha'))
1799	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.hehe:4haha'))
1800	        self.false(s_grammar.isUnivName('.4hehe'))
1801	        self.false(s_grammar.isUnivName('test:str'))
1802	        self.false(s_grammar.isUnivName('test:str.hehe'))
1803	        self.false(s_grammar.isUnivName('test:str.hehe:haha'))
1804	        self.false(s_grammar.isUnivName('test:str.haha.hehe'))
1805	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.foo:x'))
1806	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('.x:foo'))
1807	        self.true(s_grammar.isUnivName('._haha'))
1808	
1809	        self.true(s_grammar.isFormName('test:str'))
1810	        self.true(s_grammar.isFormName('t2:str'))
1811	        self.true(s_grammar.isFormName('test:str:yup'))
1812	        self.true(s_grammar.isFormName('test:str123'))
1813	        self.false(s_grammar.isFormName('test'))
1814	        self.false(s_grammar.isFormName('2t:str'))
1815	        self.false(s_grammar.isFormName('.hehe'))
1816	        self.false(s_grammar.isFormName('testcmd'))
1817	        self.true(s_grammar.isFormName('x:foo'))
1818	        self.true(s_grammar.isFormName('foo:x'))
1819	
1820	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str'))
1821	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str:tick'))
1822	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str:_tick'))
1823	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('_test:str:_tick'))
1824	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str:str123'))
1825	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str:123str'))
1826	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str:123:456'))
1827	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str.hehe'))
1828	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str.hehe'))
1829	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str.hehe.haha'))
1830	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:str.hehe:haha'))
1831	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('test:x'))
1832	        self.true(s_grammar.isPropName('x:x'))
1833	        self.false(s_grammar.isPropName('test'))
1834	        self.false(s_grammar.isPropName('2t:str'))
1835	        self.false(s_grammar.isPropName('.hehe'))
1836	        self.false(s_grammar.isPropName('testcmd'))
1837	
1838	    async def test_embed_offsets(self):
1839	
1840	        embq = ' /* secret comment */ $lib.print(hello) /* haha */ $lib.print(goodbye) /*foo */ '
1841	        query = f'$q = ${{{embq}}} $lib.print($q)'
1842	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1843	        q = parser.query()
1844	        embed = q.kids[0].kids[1]
1845	        self.eq(embq, embed.getAstText())
1846	
1847	def gen_parse_list():
1848	    '''
1849	    Prints out the Asts for a list of queries in order to compare ASTs between versions of parsers
1850	    '''
1851	    retn = []
1852	    for i, query in enumerate(Queries):
1853	        parser = s_parser.Parser(query)
1854	        tree = parser.query()
1855	        retn.append(str(tree))
1856	    return retn
1857	
1858	def print_parse_list():
1859	    for i in gen_parse_list():
1860	        print(f'    {repr(i)},')
1861	
1862	if __name__ == '__main__':
1863	    print_parse_list()
